President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Maryland and ordered federal aid to help with the aftermath of Hurricane Irene. The Department of Homeland Security and FEMA will coordinate disaster relief efforts to provide assistance and support to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. The federal government will provide 75% of the funding for emergency protective measures. Thomas J. McCool has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.